Script I used for work.
It has many applicaitons as it was used frequently 

This Python script enables automated email sending through Gmail's SMTP server. 
It leverages the smtplib library to establish a secure connection to Gmail's SMTP server and the email.mime.


text module to construct and format email messages.
The script allows users to specify the email subject, body, sender's email address, sender's password, and recipient's email address as input parameters. 

By utilizing this script, users can easily automate the process of sending emails from their Gmail accounts,

If you are on linux be sure to fallow the notes in the script

If on windows simply run the sccript with task scheduler or on your server for simple automation
